<TITLE> President opens 'Digital Bangladesh' meet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com) President Zillur Rahman inaugurated the Digital Bangladesh Conference, 2009 on Sunday with a call for expansion of Internet technology across the country. The government will introduce IT in the country's schools, colleges and universities as part of educational curricullum, the president told the conference, organised by the Bangladesh Computer Society. Private as well as non-governmental organisations will have to support the government initiative of spreading IT in the country, Zillur stressed. He said today's modern world has become dependent on IT, which has already brought changes in the society. "The developing countries will have to catch up with others," he added. Zillur said for overall development the prime minister has given guidelines for turning the country into "digital Bangladesh" by 2021, when the nation will celebrate its golden jubilee. The IT sector will play a crucial role in alleviating poverty as well as contribute to socio-economic and cultural development, he said. The sector will help realise Bangabandhu's cherished dream of a golden Bangladesh, said Zillur. Textiles and jute minister Abdul Latif Siddiqui, information and cultural affairs minister Abul Kalam Azad and Computer society president Mostafa Jabbar also spoke on the occasion
